Redesign the preservation status indicators on the resource show page

comments.body:
![HealthReportModal.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cba15f2e89c9c3b0c58e0d1/978dac55-bcc8-42af-b9c6-c3daf9a257cd)

Link to find/fix goes to File Manager. Screenshot of File Manager error indicators coming soon.

This is looking nice to me; it would be good to also have a variant where the derivatives aren't healthy.

I'm still concerned that giving a date for the last fixity check could be misleading to users; they might think the whole resource was checked on that day when in reality the different files will have been checked on different days. Maybe it should just say, "for fixity check dates please see the file manager" with a link to that page?

there may also be some special cases around multi volume works here that we need to think about. In that case we'd need to direct folks to the individual volume resource show pages, and perhaps from there to the file manager for a given volume.

![filemanager-fixity2.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cba15f2e89c9c3b0c58e0d1/eb5be863-b3a0-4322-a601-1fb6d5aed328)

This is a first pass at error indicators on the File Manager page. I think this whole page could be redesigned but in the interest of getting this preservation work done, this mock-up is intended to be a way forward with minimal reworking. I'm struggling a bit with the indicator language since a file could potentially have problems with local, cloud, and derivatives and it would be hard to find space for all of them without extending the card element for that file and messing with the grid consistency. Also, it needs attention to color and icons, but don't want to go down that path until I get some feedback on the general approach.

I think this is looking good. The colors and icons and exclamation points all definitely call attention to the broken objects. This page would probably be the place to be able to list the last checked fixity date for both cloud and local fixity, if we want to add that. I'm also curious how "repair this file" works. Does it go to the file set page, where we have more info on what the options might be? Does it do something different for a fixity failure vs a derivative failure?

pdc_describe.title: Provenance and Messages ordered correctly; Explicit notice of backdated records; Show author UID in messages; Improve testing

comments.body: - Provenance and Messages ordered as requested: newest message at the top; oldest provenance at the top. - Sorting is now done in the ERB, rather than the model, since the two rendering cases have different behavior. - Moving the sort out of the model required tweaks to a handful of other tests: These really only care about the set membership, not the order, so these changes are not substantive. - Explicit notice of backdated records, with `updated_at` used to record the actual date, and `created_at` used for the back-dated date. Happy to swap if these are not the desired semantics - Show author UID in messages. Partially addresses #863. - Two view tests, corresponding to the two partials, that cover the features listed above. - I've marked this as resolving #676. Additional tweaks may be requested, but I think we've gone far enough with the provided examples.
Out of date; There's not much here, so best just to close to clean up the PR list.
